Deputy President William Ruto (pictured) will preside at the opening of the Bungoma Investment Forum today.Governor Kenneth Lusaka said more than 30 governors and 3,000 investors from around the globe will attend. International investors have already checked in at hotels in Bungoma town, and neighbouring Eldoret, Kakamega, Busia and Kitale towns. The forum provides a good platform for the movers and shakers of the business world to network, he told the press at his office yesterday.